{
  "texts": [
    "More on SVD in Compact is discussed in Appendix A",
    "For each type of projection matrix, we train LLaMA-60M with rank r = n/4.",
    "We conducted experiments using learning rates from [1e-2, 5e-3, 1e-3].",
    "All other hyperparameters were identical to those used in Section 4.1.",
    "As shown in Figure 4, using Gaussian projections with different seeds per layer slightly improved performance compared to a shared seed, suggesting that utilizing different subspaces for different layers enhances the learning capacity of the model."
  ]
}